<subSubSection pageId="2" pageNumber="273" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1437,1041,2041]" pageId="2" pageNumber="273">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,274,1041,1068]" pageId="2" pageNumber="273">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Crown (
<figureCitation box="[372,457,1042,1068]" captionStart="FIGURES 9−14" captionStartId="4.[151,264,1949,1974]" captionTargetBox="[163,1435,701,1882]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[151,1435,680,1889]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 9−14. Evanirvana aurea Hill, 1973, holotype female (USNM 01513539). 9, sternite VIII, ventral view. 10, pygofer and first valvulae, lateral view. 11, habitus, dorsal view. 12, habitus, lateral view. 13, head, ventral view. 14, specimen labels." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3516184" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3516184/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="273">Figs 11</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[470,499,1042,1068]" captionStart="FIGURES 33−44" captionStartId="8.[151,264,1907,1932]" captionTargetBox="[225,1379,166,1887]" captionTargetId="figure@8.[209,1379,166,1887]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURES 33−44. 33−36, Evanirvana aurea Hill, 1973, male. 33, dorsal habitus. 34, lateral habitus. 35, head and prothorax, dorsal view. 36, head and prothorax, lateral view. 37−40, Evanirvana tambopata sp. nov., male holotype. 37, dorsal habitus. 38, lateral habitus. 39, head and prothorax, dorsal view. 40, head and prothorax, lateral view. 41−44, Pentoffia santosi sp. nov., male holotype. 41, dorsal habitus. 42, lateral habitus. 43, head and prothorax, dorsal view. 44, head and prothorax, lateral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3516192" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3516192/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="273">33</figureCitation>
) with anterior margin rounded; pale yellow with a W-shaped dark macula on apical half. Aedeagus (
<figureCitation box="[333,432,1078,1105]" captionStart="FIGURES 1−8" captionStartId="3.[151,264,1937,1962]" captionTargetBox="[204,1379,180,1917]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[198,1389,166,1917]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 1−8. Evanirvana aurea Hill, 1973, male. 1, head, ventral view. 2, forewing. 3, pygofer, valve, subgenital plate, and anal tube, lateral view. 4, subgenital plate, ventral view. 5, connective and styles, dorsal view. 6, style, lateral view. 7, aedeagus, lateral view. 8, aedeagus, caudal view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3516182" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3516182/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="273">Figs 7, 8</figureCitation>
) with shaft depressed dorsoventrally; laterally expanded at apical third, with pair of short lateral preapical processes; apex broadly rounded. Female sternite VII (
<figureCitation box="[959,1027,1114,1140]" captionStart="FIGURES 9−14" captionStartId="4.[151,264,1949,1974]" captionTargetBox="[163,1435,701,1882]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[151,1435,680,1889]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 9−14. Evanirvana aurea Hill, 1973, holotype female (USNM 01513539). 9, sternite VIII, ventral view. 10, pygofer and first valvulae, lateral view. 11, habitus, dorsal view. 12, habitus, lateral view. 13, head, ventral view. 14, specimen labels." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3516184" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3516184/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="273">Fig. 9</figureCitation>
) with posterolateral angles reduced, posterior margin with a short median lobe. Female pygofer (
<figureCitation box="[822,903,1150,1176]" captionStart="FIGURES 9−14" captionStartId="4.[151,264,1949,1974]" captionTargetBox="[163,1435,701,1882]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[151,1435,680,1889]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 9−14. Evanirvana aurea Hill, 1973, holotype female (USNM 01513539). 9, sternite VIII, ventral view. 10, pygofer and first valvulae, lateral view. 11, habitus, dorsal view. 12, habitus, lateral view. 13, head, ventral view. 14, specimen labels." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3516184" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3516184/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="273">Fig. 10</figureCitation>
) with posterior margin broadly rounded, except for a slight dorsal concavity. First valvula (
<figureCitation box="[629,709,1186,1212]" captionStart="FIGURES 9−14" captionStartId="4.[151,264,1949,1974]" captionTargetBox="[163,1435,701,1882]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[151,1435,680,1889]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 9−14. Evanirvana aurea Hill, 1973, holotype female (USNM 01513539). 9, sternite VIII, ventral view. 10, pygofer and first valvulae, lateral view. 11, habitus, dorsal view. 12, habitus, lateral view. 13, head, ventral view. 14, specimen labels." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3516184" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3516184/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="273">Fig. 10</figureCitation>
) short, not exceeding pygofer apex. Second valvulae (
<bibRefCitation author="Hill, B. G." box="[1314,1431,1186,1212]" pageId="2" pageNumber="273" pagination="78 - 79" refId="ref5589" refString="Hill, B. G. (1973) A new genus of Cicadellidae from Brazil. Proceedings of the Entomological Society of Washington, 75 (1), 78 - 79." type="journal article" year="1973">Hill, 1973</bibRefCitation>
; Figs C, D) with 5–7 irregular dorsoapical teeth.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="2" pageNumber="273" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1437,1041,2041]" box="[199,1020,1257,1285]" pageId="2" pageNumber="273">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,345,1257,1284]" pageId="2" pageNumber="273">Description.</emphasis>
Measurements (mm). Total length: 7.0 (male), 8.5 (female).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1437,1041,2041]" pageId="2" pageNumber="273">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,335,1293,1320]" pageId="2" pageNumber="273">Coloration.</emphasis>
Pale yellow (
<figureCitation box="[486,612,1294,1320]" captionStart="FIGURES 9−14" captionStartId="4.[151,264,1949,1974]" captionTargetBox="[163,1435,701,1882]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[151,1435,680,1889]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 9−14. Evanirvana aurea Hill, 1973, holotype female (USNM 01513539). 9, sternite VIII, ventral view. 10, pygofer and first valvulae, lateral view. 11, habitus, dorsal view. 12, habitus, lateral view. 13, head, ventral view. 14, specimen labels." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3516184" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3516184/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="273">Figs 11, 12</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[623,696,1294,1320]" captionStart="FIGURES 33−44" captionStartId="8.[151,264,1907,1932]" captionTargetBox="[225,1379,166,1887]" captionTargetId="figure@8.[209,1379,166,1887]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURES 33−44. 33−36, Evanirvana aurea Hill, 1973, male. 33, dorsal habitus. 34, lateral habitus. 35, head and prothorax, dorsal view. 36, head and prothorax, lateral view. 37−40, Evanirvana tambopata sp. nov., male holotype. 37, dorsal habitus. 38, lateral habitus. 39, head and prothorax, dorsal view. 40, head and prothorax, lateral view. 41−44, Pentoffia santosi sp. nov., male holotype. 41, dorsal habitus. 42, lateral habitus. 43, head and prothorax, dorsal view. 44, head and prothorax, lateral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3516192" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3516192/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="273">33, 34</figureCitation>
). Crown (
<figureCitation box="[805,889,1294,1320]" captionStart="FIGURES 9−14" captionStartId="4.[151,264,1949,1974]" captionTargetBox="[163,1435,701,1882]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[151,1435,680,1889]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 9−14. Evanirvana aurea Hill, 1973, holotype female (USNM 01513539). 9, sternite VIII, ventral view. 10, pygofer and first valvulae, lateral view. 11, habitus, dorsal view. 12, habitus, lateral view. 13, head, ventral view. 14, specimen labels." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3516184" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3516184/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="273">Figs 11</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[900,929,1293,1320]" captionStart="FIGURES 33−44" captionStartId="8.[151,264,1907,1932]" captionTargetBox="[225,1379,166,1887]" captionTargetId="figure@8.[209,1379,166,1887]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURES 33−44. 33−36, Evanirvana aurea Hill, 1973, male. 33, dorsal habitus. 34, lateral habitus. 35, head and prothorax, dorsal view. 36, head and prothorax, lateral view. 37−40, Evanirvana tambopata sp. nov., male holotype. 37, dorsal habitus. 38, lateral habitus. 39, head and prothorax, dorsal view. 40, head and prothorax, lateral view. 41−44, Pentoffia santosi sp. nov., male holotype. 41, dorsal habitus. 42, lateral habitus. 43, head and prothorax, dorsal view. 44, head and prothorax, lateral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3516192" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3516192/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="273">35</figureCitation>
) with a W-shaped dark macula on apical half. Forewing hyaline white (
<figureCitation box="[433,502,1330,1356]" captionStart="FIGURES 1−8" captionStartId="3.[151,264,1937,1962]" captionTargetBox="[204,1379,180,1917]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[198,1389,166,1917]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 1−8. Evanirvana aurea Hill, 1973, male. 1, head, ventral view. 2, forewing. 3, pygofer, valve, subgenital plate, and anal tube, lateral view. 4, subgenital plate, ventral view. 5, connective and styles, dorsal view. 6, style, lateral view. 7, aedeagus, lateral view. 8, aedeagus, caudal view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3516182" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3516182/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="273">Fig. 2</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[514,543,1330,1356]" captionStart="FIGURES 9−14" captionStartId="4.[151,264,1949,1974]" captionTargetBox="[163,1435,701,1882]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[151,1435,680,1889]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 9−14. Evanirvana aurea Hill, 1973, holotype female (USNM 01513539). 9, sternite VIII, ventral view. 10, pygofer and first valvulae, lateral view. 11, habitus, dorsal view. 12, habitus, lateral view. 13, head, ventral view. 14, specimen labels." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3516184" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3516184/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="273">11</figureCitation>
), male with a dark brown longitudinal band extending from mid-clavus to halflength of apical cells, narrow at base and widening towards apex.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1437,1041,2041]" box="[199,1037,1401,1428]" pageId="2" pageNumber="273">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,461,1402,1428]" pageId="2" pageNumber="273">External morphology.</emphasis>
Crown (
<figureCitation box="[559,644,1402,1428]" captionStart="FIGURES 9−14" captionStartId="4.[151,264,1949,1974]" captionTargetBox="[163,1435,701,1882]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[151,1435,680,1889]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 9−14. Evanirvana aurea Hill, 1973, holotype female (USNM 01513539). 9, sternite VIII, ventral view. 10, pygofer and first valvulae, lateral view. 11, habitus, dorsal view. 12, habitus, lateral view. 13, head, ventral view. 14, specimen labels." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3516184" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3516184/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="273">Figs 11</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[656,685,1401,1428]" captionStart="FIGURES 33−44" captionStartId="8.[151,264,1907,1932]" captionTargetBox="[225,1379,166,1887]" captionTargetId="figure@8.[209,1379,166,1887]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURES 33−44. 33−36, Evanirvana aurea Hill, 1973, male. 33, dorsal habitus. 34, lateral habitus. 35, head and prothorax, dorsal view. 36, head and prothorax, lateral view. 37−40, Evanirvana tambopata sp. nov., male holotype. 37, dorsal habitus. 38, lateral habitus. 39, head and prothorax, dorsal view. 40, head and prothorax, lateral view. 41−44, Pentoffia santosi sp. nov., male holotype. 41, dorsal habitus. 42, lateral habitus. 43, head and prothorax, dorsal view. 44, head and prothorax, lateral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3516192" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3516192/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="273">35</figureCitation>
) with anterior margin rounded.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1437,1041,2041]" pageId="2" pageNumber="273">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,400,1437,1464]" pageId="2" pageNumber="273">Male terminalia.</emphasis>
Pygofer (
<figureCitation box="[514,583,1438,1464]" captionStart="FIGURES 1−8" captionStartId="3.[151,264,1937,1962]" captionTargetBox="[204,1379,180,1917]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[198,1389,166,1917]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 1−8. Evanirvana aurea Hill, 1973, male. 1, head, ventral view. 2, forewing. 3, pygofer, valve, subgenital plate, and anal tube, lateral view. 4, subgenital plate, ventral view. 5, connective and styles, dorsal view. 6, style, lateral view. 7, aedeagus, lateral view. 8, aedeagus, caudal view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3516182" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3516182/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="273">Fig. 3</figureCitation>
) approximately 1.4 times higher than long; macrosetae distributed on posterior and ventral margins. Subgenital plate (
<figureCitation box="[653,720,1474,1500]" captionStart="FIGURES 1−8" captionStartId="3.[151,264,1937,1962]" captionTargetBox="[204,1379,180,1917]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[198,1389,166,1917]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 1−8. Evanirvana aurea Hill, 1973, male. 1, head, ventral view. 2, forewing. 3, pygofer, valve, subgenital plate, and anal tube, lateral view. 4, subgenital plate, ventral view. 5, connective and styles, dorsal view. 6, style, lateral view. 7, aedeagus, lateral view. 8, aedeagus, caudal view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3516182" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3516182/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="273">Fig. 3</figureCitation>
) extended beyond pygofer apex. Aedeagus (
<figureCitation box="[1220,1320,1474,1500]" captionStart="FIGURES 1−8" captionStartId="3.[151,264,1937,1962]" captionTargetBox="[204,1379,180,1917]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[198,1389,166,1917]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 1−8. Evanirvana aurea Hill, 1973, male. 1, head, ventral view. 2, forewing. 3, pygofer, valve, subgenital plate, and anal tube, lateral view. 4, subgenital plate, ventral view. 5, connective and styles, dorsal view. 6, style, lateral view. 7, aedeagus, lateral view. 8, aedeagus, caudal view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3516182" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3516182/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="273">Figs 7–8</figureCitation>
) with pair of elongate atrial processes curved dorsally, shorter than shaft length; shaft depressed dorsoventrally, laterally expanded at apical third with short lateral preapical processes, anteroventrally directed, about one-fifth shaft length; apex broadly rounded.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1437,1041,2041]" pageId="2" pageNumber="273">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,427,1617,1644]" pageId="2" pageNumber="273">Female terminalia.</emphasis>
Sternite VII (
<figureCitation box="[589,659,1618,1644]" captionStart="FIGURES 9−14" captionStartId="4.[151,264,1949,1974]" captionTargetBox="[163,1435,701,1882]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[151,1435,680,1889]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 9−14. Evanirvana aurea Hill, 1973, holotype female (USNM 01513539). 9, sternite VIII, ventral view. 10, pygofer and first valvulae, lateral view. 11, habitus, dorsal view. 12, habitus, lateral view. 13, head, ventral view. 14, specimen labels." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3516184" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3516184/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="273">Fig. 9</figureCitation>
) 2.4 times wider than long; posterolateral angles reduced, posterior margin with a short median lobe. Female pygofer (
<figureCitation box="[725,807,1654,1680]" captionStart="FIGURES 9−14" captionStartId="4.[151,264,1949,1974]" captionTargetBox="[163,1435,701,1882]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[151,1435,680,1889]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 9−14. Evanirvana aurea Hill, 1973, holotype female (USNM 01513539). 9, sternite VIII, ventral view. 10, pygofer and first valvulae, lateral view. 11, habitus, dorsal view. 12, habitus, lateral view. 13, head, ventral view. 14, specimen labels." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3516184" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3516184/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="273">Fig. 10</figureCitation>
) short; dorsal margin straight; posterior margin broadly rounded, except for a slight dorsal concavity; macrosetae distributed in the apical third. First valvula (
<figureCitation box="[1278,1359,1690,1716]" captionStart="FIGURES 9−14" captionStartId="4.[151,264,1949,1974]" captionTargetBox="[163,1435,701,1882]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[151,1435,680,1889]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 9−14. Evanirvana aurea Hill, 1973, holotype female (USNM 01513539). 9, sternite VIII, ventral view. 10, pygofer and first valvulae, lateral view. 11, habitus, dorsal view. 12, habitus, lateral view. 13, head, ventral view. 14, specimen labels." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3516184" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3516184/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="273">Fig. 10</figureCitation>
) short, not exceeding pygofer apex; slightly curved dorsally, about 11 times longer than high; dorsal sculptured area starting on apical third; apex acute. For other features see 
<bibRefCitation author="Hill, B. G." box="[709,838,1762,1788]" pageId="2" pageNumber="273" pagination="78 - 79" refId="ref5589" refString="Hill, B. G. (1973) A new genus of Cicadellidae from Brazil. Proceedings of the Entomological Society of Washington, 75 (1), 78 - 79." type="journal article" year="1973">Hill (1973)</bibRefCitation>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
